Business Brief -- Turner Corp.:
   Quarterly Loss Narrowed;
   Earnings Posted for Year
For the year, Turner posted net income of $11.3 million,
or $2.06 a share, against a net loss of $10.8 million, or
$2.41 a share, in 1990. The 1990 loss was due to a $21
million pretax reserve against the company's real estate
portfolio. The company additionally had a $29.8 million
pretax gain in 1991 from a curtailment of the company's
defined benefits plan.
   The value of construction completed for the year was down
18% to $2.67 billion from $3.26 billion.